                    '4' => 'Balanced evacuation management: implements a phased approach — immediate evacuation of cabins closest to 9147 (priority zone of 20-30 cabins) using cabin stewards for door-to-door notification rather than PA alarm (reducing panic), simultaneously prepares for full Zone 7 evacuation if fire is confirmed, positions medical team at evacuation route with wheelchair and mobility assistance, pre-identifies the muster area for displaced passengers (a lounge on Deck 10), Hotel Director coordinates crew at evacuation routes to assist elderly passengers, fire team enters cabin 9147 to confirm or deny fire while evacuation of adjacent cabins proceeds.',
                    '5' => 'Expert evacuation decision: implements immediate, phased, controlled evacuation recognising that a 15-minute-old potential cabin fire leaves no room for delay — Phase 1: steward-assisted door-to-door evacuation of 20 cabins nearest to 9147 beginning immediately (no PA alarm, personal contact, assistance for mobility-impaired), Phase 2: zone-selective PA for remainder of Deck 9 Zone 7 corridor triggered if fire team confirms fire or if smoke becomes visible, Phase 3: adjacent zones placed on standby alert, fire boundaries established per fire safety plan to contain any spread. Concurrently: fire team makes entry to cabin 9147 for assessment and firefighting, HVAC fire dampers closed for Zone 7 to prevent smoke migration, drencher system armed for activation, medical team deployed with stretchers and cardiac equipment at evacuation collection point, Hotel Director ensures all displaced passengers accounted for and provided with blankets and support in pre-identified lounge, entire response timeline documented on VDR and bridge log.',
